				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Chroma in both NTSC and PAL is sent on a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quadrature_amplitude_modulation" class="postlink">QAM</a> signal. To isolate chroma from the rest of the signal, use a bandpass filter centered about the carrier frequency. For NTSC, this might be a bandpass allowing 3.0-4.2 MHz.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

