				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That's what I'm talking about. I know where it is, and how to get it with &quot;perfect&quot; stuff, like fourier transforms etc. But analog device does work completely different. It can't see future, to perform perfect bandpass. And as you should know bandpass is equal to lowpass+highpass. Also, lowpass is enough to get Y component.<br /><br />I know what is QAM and how to decode it in &quot;perfect&quot; maner again, but it's analog device, it works different. For example no ringing on borders (steps), only glitch transition, but no after-effects except maybe some particular cases.<br /><br />That's why I'm asking about analog lowpass, comming in TV, and how other things made there in most of cases.</div>

